                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-142-off746 t18220911-142-crimeloc749"></join>. On the 17th of August, I left the house about half-past six in the evening, to go into the privy, leaving 
               <persName id="t18220911-142-person1352">
                  John 
                  Davis
               <interp inst="t18220911-142-person1352" type="surname" value="Davis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-142-person1352" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220911-142-person1352" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and other servants, in doors; the area door was shut, and the latch was down. While there, I saw the prisoner come down into the area, open the door, and go into the passage. He unlocked the housekeeper's room door, (the key was in the door,) and went in. I came out of the privy as quick as I could, and met him coming out of the room into the area, with these towels under his arm. I seized him; he begged for mercy. I took him into the kitchen; he there dropped them - they are worth 14 s. I sent for an officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220911-142-person1353">
